Item 1.01 Entry into a Material Definitive Agreement.
On July 6, 2005, Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (the "Company") entered into a Loan Modification Agreement with Silicon Valley Bank (the "Bank"), thereby amending the Loan and Security Agreement dated May 10, 2002 (the "Original Agreement") between the Company and the Bank. The Original Agreement which provided the Company with a $25 million revolving line of credit has been modified effective July 7, 2005 to (a) provide the Company with a $40 million revolving line of credit, (b) extend the maturity date on such line of credit to July 6, 2006, and (c) amend other terms, including terms related to non-usage fees and financial covenants. No amount is currently outstanding under the line of credit, and the Company has not drawn upon such facility since the first quarter of 2001; however, the Company relies upon the credit facility as a principal source of liquidity and to secure letters of credit issued on its behalf from time to time.
Any advances under the Original Agreement, as amended, will bear interest at the prime rate (6.25% at July 12, 2005) minus 1%.
A copy of the Loan Modification Agreement has been attached to this Current Report on Form 8-K as Exhibit 10.1.
