Item 1.01 Entry into a Material Definitive Agreement
     On October 3, 2005, Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (the ) and MKS Instruments, Inc. and its subsidiary, Applied Science and Technology, Inc. (together, ) executed a Settlement Agreement in connection with patent infringement litigation pending between the Company and MKS relating to the Company's Xstream and Rapid plasma generator products. Pursuant to the Settlement Agreement, the Company has paid MKS $3 million in cash. Additionally, the Company and MKS have stipulated to a final judgment of infringement and an injunction prohibiting the Company from making, using, selling, offering to sell, or importing into the United States its Rapid, Rapid FE, Rapid OE and Xstream products, except as provided in the Settlement Agreement. Sales of these products have accounted for less than 5% of the Company's total sales each year since the introduction of such products.
""
Company
"MKS"
     The foregoing is a summary of the material terms of the Settlement Agreement. A copy of such agreement is filed as an exhibit to this Current Report on Form 8-K, and the terms of such agreement are incorporated herein by reference.
