Item 8.01 Other Events.
On December 24, 2007, the Board of Directors of Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (the "Company") authorized the repurchase of up to $75 million of the Company's common stock over the next 12 months. Purchases under the program may be made from time-to-time in the open market, through privately negotiated transactions, through block trades, Rule 10b5-1 trading plans or other available means. There is no minimum number of shares to be repurchased under the program and the program may be discontinued at any time. Purchases under the program will depend upon the availability of cash, as well as prevailing general economic and stock market conditions.
