y shall not, except with the prior written consent of the Acquiror, make any payment with respect to, or settle or offer to settle, any such demands, with respect to any holder of Dissenting Shares before the Effective Time. Notwithstanding the foregoing, as provided in , it is a condition to the Acquiror's obligations pursuant to this Agreement that holders of Company Shares representing in excess of 95% of the issued and outstanding Company Shares immediately prior to the Effective Time shall not have demanded payment or exercised appraisal rights under applicable provisions of Oregon Law.
