SECTION 9.4.
Notice of Claim.
          (a) If any action is brought against any Person entitled to indemnification pursuant to or (a ""), in respect of a claim under or (an ""), the Claimant shall promptly notify the liable party therefore (the "") in writing of the institution of such Indemnifiable Claim (but the failure to so notify the Indemnifying Party shall not relieve the Indemnifying Party from any liability the Indemnifying Party may have except to the extent such failure prejudices the Indemnifying Party); provided, however, the Parties agree to provide such notice as soon as reasonably commercially practicable. If a Claimant becomes aware of a possible Indemnifiable Claim (before the institution of such Indemnifiable Claim which is addressed in the preceding sentence and which proceeding sentence shall govern upon the institution of such Indemnifiable Claim), the Claimant shall use its commercially reasonable efforts to promptly notify the Indemnifying Party in writing of Claimant's knowledge of such possible Indemnifiable Claim.
