Item 8.01 Other Events.
On April 27, 2010, Douglas S. Schatz, the Chairman of the Board of Directors of Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (the ""), and his wife Jill E. Schatz, as trustees of The Douglas S. Schatz and Jill E. Schatz Family Trust U/A DTD 3/26/02 (the ""), adopted a selling plan pursuant to Rule 10b5-1 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the ""), which provides for the sale of up to a total of $9,000,000 in shares of common stock of the Company beginning May 12, 2010. Shares will be sold under the Plan on the open market at prevailing market prices and subject to minimum price thresholds specified in such Plan. The Plan will terminate on July 30, 2010, even if all shares subject to the Plan have not been sold. The Plan was established as part of the Mr. and Mrs. Schatz's personal long term strategy for asset diversification and liquidity. Rule 10b5-1 permits officers and directors of public companies to adopt pre-determined plans for buying or selling specified amounts of stock if the plan is adopted at a time when the purchaser or seller is not aware of any material non-public information.
