Schedule 5.1
no later than the times specified therein, 1) agree that no Domestic Subsidiary of a Loan Party (except to the extent that a Domestic Subsidiary acquired in a Permitted Acquisition has a different fiscal year) will have a fiscal year different from that of Borrower, 1) agree to maintain a system of accounting that enables Borrower to produce financial statements in accordance with GAAP, and 1) agree that they will (1) keep a reporting system that shows all additions, sales, claims, returns, and allowances with respect to their sales, and (1) maintain its billing systems and practices substantially as in effect as of the Closing Date and shall only make material modifications thereto with notice to, and with the consent of, Agent.
