 means a swap agreement as that term is defined in Section 101(53B)(A) of the Bankruptcy Code.
Hedge Obligations
 means any and all obligations or liabilities, whether absolute or contingent, due or to become due, now existing or hereafter arising, of Parent or its Domestic Subsidiaries arising under, owing pursuant to, or existing in respect of Hedge Agreements entered into with one or more of the Hedge Providers.
