Sanctioned Entity
 means 1) a country or a government of a country, 1) an agency of the government of a country, 1) an organization directly or indirectly controlled by a country or its government, 1) a Person resident in or determined to be resident in a country, in each case, that is subject to a country sanctions program administered and enforced by OFAC.
Sanctioned Person
 means a person named on the list of Specially Designated Nationals maintained by OFAC.
