). The review of the Draft P&L Statements and the Draft Earn-out Calculation shall be restricted to whether the Draft P&L Statements and the Draft Earn-out Calculation comply with the requirements set forth in Sections 6.1 and 6.2. The Earn-out Review Period commences with receipt by the Seller of the Draft P&L Statements and the Draft Earn-out Calculation. Any objections of the Seller to the Draft P&L Statements and the Draft Earn-out Calculation shall be notified to the Purchaser and the Parent Company specifying in writing each individual item in dispute and sufficient reasons for such objections. To the extent that the Seller does not duly notify any objections to the Draft P&L Statements and the Draft Earn-out Calculation within the Earn-out Review Period, the Draft P&L Statements and/or the Draft Earn-out Calculation shall become final and binding upon the Parties upon expiration of the Earn-out Review Period.
